  "uncertainty_notes": "Gaza combatant-share estimates are the largest uncertainty. This report explicitly rejects use of Israeli MOD/IDF public militant-killed claims such as ~17,000 or ~25,000+ as the central estimate or floor; those are belligerent_claim values and are inconsistent with several independent demographic and verification analyses unless nearly all working-age male deaths are treated as combatants. The Gaza civilian/combatant range is derived from identified-death age/sex structure, OHCHR verification, AOAV/Spagat reasoning, peer-reviewed mortality work, and leaked-database reporting; unverified 'militant' deaths are not automatically assigned to Hamas. Indirect deaths are also highly uncertain: the measured 2026 Lancet Global Health excess non-violent estimate through 5 January 2025 is far narrower than the broader 2024 Lancet projection, which could imply roughly 149,000 indirect Gaza deaths but is a scenario rather than a confirmed count.",
